      "id": "a1808bf3_786441b3",
      "file_path": "k8s/ChangeLog.md",
      "patchset_number": 3,
      "line": 10,
      "message": "1.4.6 specifically adds two features:\n-- Support for specifying CPU and memory resources in a blueprint for a containerized component\n-- Changes the default time that the plugin will wait for a container to become ready from 300 seconds to 1800 seconds\n\nShould make this clear in the changelog.  The JIRA referenced here is very broad.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 511,
        "name": "Jack Lucas",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jflos@sonoris.net",
        "username": "jackl"
      },
      "updated": "2019-02-27 14:25:13.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "802f3eb0_df43c4bd",
      "file_path": "k8s/k8s-node-type.yaml",
      "patchset_number": 3,
      "line": 126,
      "message": "I suggest adding a link to the k8s documentation for resources.  (https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/configuration/manage-compute-resources-container/ is a good one.)  Also point out that we expect to see a \"requests\" property and/or a \"limits\" property, with subproproperties for cpu and memory.",
